    <para id="para-00005">Calculating NPV is simply a time value of money problem in which each cash flow is discounted back to the present value. If we assume that the cost of funds for Sam’s is 9%, then the NPV can be calculated as</para>
    <equation id="eq-00002"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mtable columnspacing="0px" columnalign="right center left"><mtr><mtd><mi>NPV</mi><mo> </mo></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></mrow><msup><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09</mn></mrow><mn>6</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>-</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>16,000</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>1,834.86</mn><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>3,366.72</mn><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>3,860.92</mn><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>3,542.13</mn><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>3,249.66</mn><mo> </mo><mo>+</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>2,981.34</mn><mo> </mo><mo>-</mo><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>16,000</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo> </mo><mo>$</mo><mn>2,835.63</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/><mtd/><mtd/></mtr></mtable></math></equation>
    <para id="para-00006" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">Because the NPV is positive, Sam’s Sporting Goods should purchase the embroidery machine. The value of the firm will increase by $2,835.63 as a result of accepting the project.</para>
    <para id="para-00007">Calculating NPV involves computing the present value of each cash flow and then summing the present values of all cash flows from the project. This project has six future cash flows, so six present values must be computed. Although this is not difficult, it is tedious.</para>
    <para id="para-00008">A financial calculator is able to calculate a series of present values in the background for you, automating much of the process. You simply have to provide the calculator with each cash flow, the time period in which each cash flow occurs, and the discount rate that you want to use to discount the future cash flows to the present.</para>
